Package com.googlecode.biscotti.collect

This package contains interfaces, implementations, and other utilities for working with Collections and Maps.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BoundedMap<K,V> A capacity restricted Map.
BoundedQueue<E> A capacity restricted Queue.
SortedCollection<E> A Collection that further provides a total ordering on its elements.
SortedList<E> A List that further provides a total ordering on its elements.
 

Class Summary
Collections3 Static utility methods which operate on or return Collections and Maps.
FIFOMap<K,V> A LinkedHashMap implementation of BoundedMap which removes stale mappings in first-in-first-out order.
ForwardingDeque<E> A Deque which forwards all its method calls to another Deque.
ForwardingNavigableMap<K,V> A NavigableMap which forwards all its method calls to another NavigableMap.
ForwardingNavigableSet<E> A NavigableSet which forwards all its method calls to another NavigableSet.
ForwardingPeekingIterator<E> A PeekingIterator which forwards all its method calls to another PeekingIterator.
ForwardingSortedList<E> A SortedList which forwards all its method calls to another SortedList.
Iterables2 Static utility methods which operate on or return Iterables.
Iterators2 Static utility methods which operate on or return Iterators.
LinkedBoundedQueue<E> A linked list implementation of BoundedQueue.
LRUMap<K,V> A LinkedHashMap implementation of BoundedMap which removes stale mappings in least-recently-accessed order.
RankList<E> A List optimized for efficient random access insertion and removal operations.
SkipList<E> A List whose elements are sorted from least to greatest according to their natural ordering, or by an explicit Comparator provided at creation.
TreeBoundedQueue<E> An implementation of BoundedQueue backed by a TreeQueue.
TreeDeque<E> An unbounded priority Deque based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
TreeList<E> A SortedList implementation, based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
TreeQueue<E> An unbounded priority Queue based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
UnmodifiableListIterator<E> A ListIterator that does not support remove(), add(), and set(E).
UnmodifiablePeekingIterator<E> A PeekingIterator that does not support remove().
